The paper discusses the design of next-generation wireless communication systems with strict constraints on latency and reliability, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also analyzes the trade-off between channel estimation and data codeword length, which involves system-level considerations and optimization (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses accurate models of the physical layer and queueing analysis, which are relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
